    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.32b" />
                
                <fw type="imprint">
                    <figure>
                        <figDesc>A lighthouse, with curled waves on either side</figDesc>
                        <p><unclear/></p>
                    </figure>
                    
                    <hi rend="caps">HOTEL TRAYMORE
                        <lb/>
                    ATLANTIC CITY, N.J.</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>September 26, 1924.</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Doctor Neihardt:</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Both of your kind letters received and of course I approve the proposition with regard to Crazy Horse. If in the country, I shall be glad to contribute my <unclear>poor</unclear> services in any way, although I presume that most of the younger officers of the army would today say with Gen. Sheridan: "The only good Indian is a dead Indian."</p>
                
                <p>I leave for New York in a few days and expect to go to
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">32</fw>
                    
                    <pb facs="nei.j4a.11.32a"/>
                    
                    Havana for several months, I have even thought of living in Nice (France), where I have some good friends. My safest address for the present is "Army and Navy Club Washington, <hi rend="caps">D.C.</hi>"</p>
                
                <p>I enclose a list of the <unclear>members</unclear> of the "Order of Indian Wars," Capt. Meade, The Recorder, had only one list which he loaned to me and I copied. Later, when the fall addresses are in the Army Directory, I will send you a copy</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>With kindest regards,</salute>
                    <salute>Most faithfully yours,</salute>
                    
                    <signed>H.R. Lemly</signed>
                    <note type="curatorial">Temly</note>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
